@node "DISABLED" "Disabled features of the program..."
                             Disabled Features
                             =================
    As with all programs, some of the features have been altered/disabled to
help make the program more tempting to subscribe. I dont believe in
rendering the program crippled, as this is an offput to the purchaser. I
have mainly disabled some routines.

    I have placed an "Annoying Requester" in the code of the program, which
pops up quite a lot and waits for you to click the button. This is of course
removed in the @{"registered version" link "REGISTER" 0}.

    Each time the program amends or enters a new record, a temporary file is
created for each of the index's the program can search through. I have
purposely made this file copy the contents to a disk file, instead of RAM
for the extra speed. This slows operation down, especially after around 20
records are stored. In the prefs files on the registered version, you can
set this to RAM: or to a disk file.

    When it comes to entering a new file, only personal files can be entered
for the moment. Business ones are available in the registered  version of
the program.

    Printers in the program can be altered, to either a serial, parrarell or
a file. The PRT: device can also be used. In this demo, the PRT: device is
the printer driver, and cannot be changed.

    I have removed the directory from the program. The directory allows you
to look at the list of entrants, rather like the standard phonebook. The
program will still allow you to edit/amend records as normal.

    Just to be arkward, I have disabled the DELETE RECORD entry. It will ask
for input as normal, and when it comes to deleting it from the disk it wont
do it. I feel a delete option isnt really needed in a program like this.

    Only the @{"TELEPHONE index" link "SEARCH" 0} is saved to the disk and searched. It will save
all telephone, fax, and employer phone/fax telephone numbers. All temporary
files also will be stored in T: drive.
@endnode

@node "INSTALLATION" "Installing the program correctly..."
                               Installation
                               ============

    In order for the program to run correctly, a few things may have to be
done in order for it to work right. If you have the version without the
library compiled into the executable, then the AMOS.LIBRARY file will be
needed in LIBS: to run. The program uses an assign to the volume DATA_DISK:
which is used by all my database programs. If the program detects this
assign, the PhonebookV3 drawer, and all the smaller drawers will be made by
the system automatically. The file QUICK_ASSIGN will make an assign to the
@{"example drawer" link "EXAMPLE" 0}, so you can have a quick look through that.

    The program has been designed for best use on a HD system, for speed of
disk access when it comes to the index files. @{"Certain features have been" link "DISABLED" 0}
@{"removed from the program" link "DISABLED" 0}, or altered, and are fully working in the complete
registered version. The program will not function without the DATA_DISK:
volume mounted. Floppies can be used, but a HD is recomended more.
@endnode

@node "INTRODUCTION" "Introduction to the program."
                               Introduction
                               ============

    Welcome to my new and improved phonebook program. This Amigaguide file
will explain to you exactly how to use this demonstration version of the
program. Please not that @{"some of the features have been removed" link "DISABLED" 0} from the
program, yet are complete in the @{"registered version" link "REGISTER" 0}. The program is written
with NTSC users in mind, so all systems can use it.

    This program will allow you to store large numbers of information on
individual people/companys onto your HD for easy reference in the future.
The demo version handles only personal records, and has a limited number of
search categorys. You can also @{"search the entire database for phone numbers" link "SEARCH" 0},
email address' etc. at a high speed. The system is fully mouse-controlled so
that the ease of use is always acheived. You also have a comment section on
the end of each record, in which you can make notes about the entrant so you
remember who/what they are even in a few years, and can also look up on
their record at a glance. Full printer support is featured to both serial
and parrarell printers.

    Because this program is @{"Shareware" link "SHAREWARE" 0}, it comes "As-Is" meaning that all the
files must be kept in the archive, including the examples drawer, which
contains an example database with a few entries within it so you can play
around with the system. There must be no money involved in spreading this
program, unless for a small shipping/postal charge. No changes must be made
to the executable, or its documentation.

    If you wish to use this program on a coverdisk or CD, feel free to do
so. I would be gratefull for a free copy of the magazine it appears on if
outside the UK, or email me at @{"mpd@mushy-pd.demon.co.uk" link "EMAIL" 0} giving me the
information on where it has been placced.

    Thank-you, and please enjoy the database.
@endnode

@node "REGISTER" "Registering your version of the program..."
                          Registering the program
                          =======================

    So, you have seen the program and want to register for the full version.
Not only will you get the full version of Phonebook, but a few other goodys
as well. Please continue reading.

    You will receive the full version of Phonebook V3, as well as any
updates made in the future free. If you live abroad, then you can send the
postage to receive it free. All program options will be enabled, as well as
more search options, and the business side of the database. All preferences
will be changeable, and temporary files can be stored in RAM: unless you set
it to otherwise in the prefs.

    Also in the little brown padded bag will be demo versions of some of the
other games and utilities I have written, including the latest products I am
working on. You will also receive a copy of @{"Extreme AMOS" link "EXTREMEAMOS" 0}, a disk magazine I
run, packed full of AMOS source code and tips, with tutorials on all kinds
of subjects. Definately not to be missed by any AMOS coder.

    Plus, when you become a registered user of ANY of my programs, you will
automatically be entitled to money off other programs I release in the
future, or programs I have already written. Only registered users get money
off, unless for a special reason.

    So, to get your copy of Phonebook V3, send me a cheque/postal order made
payable to Andrew Kellett for 5 pounds sterling (or 3 pounds sterling if you
are a registered user of any of my work) or the equivalent in your own
currency to this address:

                         Andrew "Mushroom" Kellett
                                @{"Mushroom PD" link "ABOUTMPD" 0}
                           32 Castleton Crescent
                                  Gamesley
                                  Glossop
                                 Derbyshire
                                  SK13 9TH
